@node Intro "Introduction"

                   @{u}What is HLconvert? What does it do?@{uu}

 HLConvert is  a little  utility with wich  you can add @{"hotlist-bookmarks" link hotlists}
 from various browsers to your favourite browser's-hotlist.

 I  wrote  HLConvert  because  I'm  using  @{"NetScape" link NetScape} a  lot  at  school and
 when I've been browing for  a  while I  usually end up with a large amount
 of  new addresses in  my  @{"NetScape" link NetScape}-hotlist.  And  I  just got  tired  of
 adding them  by  hand to my @{"IBrowse" link IBrowse}-hotlist witch I'm using at home.

 HLConvert has been tested on the following equipment:

 A1200/030/50, 540MB HD, 6MB RAM, Kickstart 3.0

   @{u}Shareware@{uu}

   The creation  and support of this and future software has taken (and will
 continue to take) a large amount of my time.

 Therefore this  product is released under the  concept of shareware  - which
 means that some extra functions are included in a @{"registered version" link Why-Register} for
 those who would like to register this product.

 Thank you.

   @{u}Final note@{uu}

   Please notice that any misspelling in this text are intentional and part
 of the art.

@endnode

@node Requirements "What do you need to run this"

   @{u}Requirements:@{uu}

   OS2.0+
   @{"reqtools.library" link ReqTools}

 If you would like to have any creative use of @{"HLConvert" link Intro} you would perhaps
 need a browser and a hotlist file to convert from...

@endnode

