@node History "History"

 @{u}History:@{uu}

 V0.3   - Only internal.

 V1.0   - Initial release. (Public)

 V1.1   - Completely rewritten the hotlist recognition routine.
          Now it should be easy to add any new hotlist formats.

        - Added support to convert @{"AMosaic" link AMosaic}-hotlists.

        - Added support to convert @{"IBrowse" link IBrowse}-hotlists
          (Good if you want to join two @{"IBrowse" link IBrowse} hotlists).

        - Added support to convert sub-menues in all formats.

        - Fixed a problem that could crash your computer if you fed
          @{"HLConvert" link HLConvert} with a very badly corrupted hotlist.
          (Now @{"HLConvert" link HLConvert} just tells you that it is corrupted)

        - Added the option @{"FAKESUB" link CLIUsage}.
          When this option is turned on and @{"HLConvert" link Intro} finds submenues
          in a submenu, @{"HLConvert" link Intro} will make fake submenues so that you
          can still keep a nice hirarchy in your hotlists.

        - Added the option @{"FAKESEP" link CLIUsage}.
          This option enables @{"HLConvert" link Intro} to convert separators from
          your @{"source-hotlist" link formats} into fake separators (For the eyes
          only!), since @{"IBrowse" link IBrowse} is not currently supporting real
          separators in the hotlist.

 V1.2   - Corrected a nasty bug in the filerequester routine.
          @{HLConvert link Intro} sometimes reported that the selected source file was not found
          even if it did infact exist. (Thanx to Fredrique for reporting that.)

        - Fixed a bug in the @{"NetScape" link NetScape}-submenu-conversion routine.
          You could get the submenu-hirarchy really messed up in some cases.
          (Amazing what a little "beq" instead of a "bne" can do...)

        - Added @{"tooltype support" link WBUsage}.
          Now you can configure @{"HLConvert" link Intro}'s default settings when run from WB.

        - Added a little "Intro"-requester wich pops up every time HLConvert
          is started. (Please don't ignore it.)

 V1.3   - MAJOR Update!!!
          Lots of parts of the code totally rewritten and cleaned up.
          The conversion routine is now rewritten again to make it easy to add
          new hotlist-formats.
          Now I should be able to add a new format in 5 mins. (Any requests?)

        - Fixed a bug in the AMosaic conversion routine.
          @{"HLConvert" link Intro} sometimes swapped the url with the description.
          (Hhmmm... Many of you noticed that one...)

        - Added the new powerful option @{"OUTTYPE" link CLIUsage}.
          Now you can convert, not only FROM any hotlist format, but also TO any format.

        - Added support to convert @{"AWeb" link AWeb}-hotlists.

        - I discovered that xMosaic and AMosaic has the same hotlist fomat
          so... Tada!!! Now HLConvert supports xMosaic also...

        - Removed the NOGUI-option... (It never did make any sense anyway!)
          If you don't want requesters to pop up on your screen then make
          sure that you specify all parameters required and you will still
          be able to use @{"HLConvert" link Intro} in a NOGUI-sort of mode.

        - Now @{"HLConvert" link Intro} warns you if you try to convert an empty hotlist.

        - Now @{"HLConvert" link Intro}'s save requester defaults to directorys and
          filenames corresponding to the format you tries to convert to.
          If you don't like this then specify @{"NODEFS" link CLIUsage} in tooltypes
          or on the commandline.

        - Now @{"HLConvert" link Intro} exists in a @{"registered" link register} version
          for those of you who would like to support me and my programming.
          Se the @{"difference" link Why-Register} between the registered & the non registed version.

        - Now @{"HLConvert" link Intro} adds itself properly to the tasklist with the
          correct name.

        - Added support to convert @{"Voyager" link Voyager}-hotlists.

        - There is a new format in version 1.01 of IBrowse. It's called IBrowse2.
          Now HLConvert supports that new format also.

        - Please notice the namechange of the author...
          I now go under the name @{b}Kristoffer Karlsson@{ub} and nothing else...

 V1.31  - When I first made @{"HLConvert" link Intro} I didn't realize that some people had
          indeed VERY big hotlists installed on their systems...
          Some of them over 100k! (Gosh! I can't really imagine the size
          of that 100k popupmenu opening on the screen... How can you have
          any practical use of that big hotlists??? Beats me... My biggest
          one is about 21k and it covers just about the whole screen)...
          However I made what I thought a "huge" 64k buffert limit in
          HLConvertV1.3... And I thought that that would never really
          be a limit to anyone..,
          Anyhow I made this little pseudo-version so that the registered
          users should be able to benefit converted hotlist with sizes up
          to 256k. That SHOULD be enough!!!

@endnode
